^-|cp||HT|f|fp||at|^b@2^Y@3When the choice is between two honor sequence length leads, the decision is never difficult. When the suits are of the same length, the stronger should be preferred; when the equally long suits are of the same strength, the one should be chosen in which the fourth or fifth card is the higher. When all cards in the two suits are exactly the same, you might just as well toss a coin. There is little justification for preferring a major suit to a minor.|
